      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence studies performed on representative screw-rod construct geometry. Peak stress and construct stiffness quantities of interest changed less than 3% between medium and fine meshes, satisfying the required convergence criterion."
    },
    {
